	)
	(text "- LowChan and HighChan are gpio outputs, controlling\n   the low and high current load drivers respectively\n- All MCU pins are connected via buses, which connect\n   to other hierarchical sheets\n- GPIO[0..4] are to be used as needed later. Connector\n   is TBD. The first 3 are capable of GPIO or PWM\n   output.\n- Channel buttons (used for debugging) are connected\n   with RC low pass filter for button debouncing.\n   Time constant is 10ms. Look at TI app note for\n   info.\n- No external pulldown on the channel inputs because\n   the load driver chip comes with them internally."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 129.54 95.885 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "bd958e98-45b5-4b55-8905-e69467b34b6a")
	)
